{
  "stem": "17135.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At night.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, then they sent us to a block.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the next morning, again, they took us all out of the block.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and besides us they had brought other people from other concentration camps-- from Buchenwald from Dachau, they all arrived more or less the same time.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had to go again across the appelplatz and again to undress.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then came Doctor Mengele.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and, and just like, like in a meat house when they look-- first grade meat, second grade meat-- they look at everybody and literally, like this-- up and down.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father-- that's the first time that we were separated from my father.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father was put, not to be gassed, to be worked until he died.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my brother and I were sent to Auschwitz III.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was called Buna.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That was a camp where the largest industrial complex of Europe was being built by 60,000 workers to produce gasoline from, from coal and Buna.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Buna was synthetic rubber because any war machine runs on parts and gasoline.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And airplanes also, they run on gasoline.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] That's really-- after we were separated, it was the last time we saw our father.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And after the war, I found out that my father was assigned to an arbeitskommando that again, carried huge excrement, human excrement to a place-- they were unloading in, in, in the barrels from the barracks.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he survived exactly one week.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was literally beaten to death.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "From a man that was part of my hometown that was assigned to stay in Auschwitz, not to go to Auschwitz III, to the other, to the work kommando.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he, for some reason, became stubendienst.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Stubendienst means in the service of the barrack.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "One-- there were always two wings.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
